मैं सिर्फ इतना ही कहूँगा जिसे ये पसंद नहीं आया और उन्हें संभलपुर और उड़ीसा को अलग अलग करके देखने का दिल कर रहा है. वो कृपा करके इसका ओरिजनल वर्जन देखें ! यहाँ अपना वक़्त काहे को बर्बाद कर रहे हो ! I think its a perfect combo of Indian Folk & Fusion. 
अब कृपया ये मत कहना ये इंडियन सांग नहीं है ये सम्भलपुरी सांग है ! फिर मुझे आपकी बुद्धि पर तरस आएगा और सिर्फ संवेदना ही प्रकट कर सकता हूँ मैं ! 
So Please...!

snippet.textDisplay: As far as I know this is not Odia but a Sambalpuri language song. Also known as Kosli language .The distance between the two is like that between Bengali and Assamese. While the arrangement is good, and while Sona's voice is sexy, the song should be sung with the 'Sambalpuri flavour' and particularly as a duet, since it is a conversation between two lovers. Also ending it with 'Bande Utkal Janani ' is like ending a Bollywood Duet with Jana Gana Mana. Catchy though this is, one hopes, other songs from that region are treated a bit exclusively........especially without Tamil Rap (excuse me).
snippet.textOriginal: As far as I know this is not Odia but a Sambalpuri language song. Also known as Kosli language .The distance between the two is like that between Bengali and Assamese. While the arrangement is good, and while Sona's voice is sexy, the song should be sung with the 'Sambalpuri flavour' and particularly as a duet, since it is a conversation between two lovers. Also ending it with 'Bande Utkal Janani ' is like ending a Bollywood Duet with Jana Gana Mana. Catchy though this is, one hopes, other songs from that region are treated a bit exclusively........especially without Tamil Rap (excuse me).
